fields.description:
 Change history search is not possible for Project Field. 

Eg: 
{code}
project changed FROM SSP To SCRUM
{code}
It returns an error:
{noformat}
History searches do not support the 'project' field.
{noformat}
Please add this capability.

According to [Managing global permissions|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver073/managing-global-permissions-861253290.html]:

{quote}
People who have the JIRA System Administrators permission can perform all of the administration functions in JIRA, while people who have only the JIRA Administrators permission cannot perform functions which could affect the application environment or network.
{quote}

I feel like this should also apply to the creation and removal of Application links in the sense that it should be restricted to Jira System Administrators. For example, app links can make use of smart commits which can potentially affect many customers, like the restricted functions of System Admins could.

Problem:

Let's say we have two instances [federated|https://confluence.atlassian.com/enterprise/federating-jira-managing-multiple-instances-461504624.html] and I have issue links from one instance (A) to another instance (B). 

 

issue 1a of instance A links to issue 1b of instance B and there is a reciprocal link

when I export issue 1a to instance b, it doesn't respect the remote links, especially if I export 1b back to instance a

 

it would be nice if Jira included the base URL of the federated issue link and then made some logical choices to add them during project or CSV import
h4. Workaround:

*The API referenced is here:*

This step will performed after the project has been imported in the target source:

[https://docs.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/api/REST/7.6.1/#api/2/issue-getRemoteIssueLinks]

*Basically we'd do a simple get from the source for all the issues in a project:*
{code:java}
GET URLOFSOURCE/rest/api/2/issue/{issueIdOrKey}/remotelink
{code}
{code:java}
    {
        "id": 10001,
        "self": "http://10.125.88.109:8080/jira730/rest/api/2/issue/KRIS-11/remotelink/10001",
        "application": {},
        "object": {
            "url": "https://docs.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/api/REST/7.6.1/#api/2/issue-getRemoteIssueLinks",
            "title": "test",
            "icon": {
                "url16x16": "https://docs.atlassian.com/favicon.ico"
            },
            "status": {
                "icon": {}
            }
        }
    }

{code}
*All you need to do is change the URL to the target instance and the call to a post, the JSON doesn't need to be reformated*
{code:java}
POST /rest/api/2/issue/{issueIdOrKey}/remotelink
{code}
{code:java}
    {
        "id": 10001,
        "self": "http://10.125.88.109:8080/jira730/rest/api/2/issue/KRIS-11/remotelink/10001",
        "application": {},
        "object": {
            "url": "https://docs.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/api/REST/7.6.1/#api/2/issue-getRemoteIssueLinks",
            "title": "test",
            "icon": {
                "url16x16": "https://docs.atlassian.com/favicon.ico"
            },
            "status": {
                "icon": {}
            }
        }
    }

{code}
